        <p>
            Unfortunately, there wasn't much to get there: Just a pair of Calvin Klein pants for me – Steffi, on the other hand, found nothing at all. After that, we continued to Ross and TJ Maxx in Estero, near US-41, and from there roughly back towards the house. We seemed to stop at every Ross, Marshall's, and TJ Maxx we encountered along the way – on the hunt for affordable, good clothing. In the end, we were successful: Steffi found several pairs of pants that not only fit but also appealed to her.
        </p>
        <p>
            While we were browsing through the stores, a thunderstorm was passing parallel to our route, heading north. It kept sending smaller and sometimes heavy rain showers our way. Between shelves and fitting rooms, we could even hear the thunder rumbling despite the music and voices – and outside, lightning occasionally flashed across the sky. Fortunately, the storm kept its distance.
        </p>

