            Back at the house, the thunderstorm had already moved on – so we jumped into the pool one more time, as a farewell to the little paradise on the canal. Afterward, we had leftovers: fried rice with chicken, and meanwhile, the washing machine was already running with our new acquisitions.
        </p>
        <p>
            As we made ourselves comfortable on the terrace afterward, it became really lively around us. Two herons landed directly on the property, apparently not afraid of humans. As I reached for the camera, a muscovy duck also waddled into the frame. And further back in the canal, a turtle was drifting, slowly passing by us – as if it too had called it a day.
        </p>
        <p>
            We spent the evening first outside on the terrace with our current series – NCIS: L.A. – but in the distance, the next thunderstorm was already announcing itself. So at some point, we moved the series time inside to the sofa, where we continued watching until it was time for bed.
        </p>
        <p>
            Tomorrow it's time to say goodbye to this beautiful house. After the big city and the pool relaxation, we're starting the third part of our journey: Welcome to the world of theme parks and tourist attractions around Orlando! It will surely be quite different – and definitely quite exciting.
